cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about improving neural machine translation using a quantization strategy tailored to the Transformer architecture. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also proposes a method for reducing computational costs, which suggests it could be relevant to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on translation tasks, which could also make it relevant to the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision), which includes image and video processing.
